# ORIG TITLE    Lightning strikes Father’s Day party in Germany . 
# ORIG CONTENT  In Germany, 39 people were injured by a lightning strike at a Father’s Day party in Dabel, a village around a 160 kilometres from Hamburg. Eight of the wounded are believed to be in serious condition. Several trees and a electrical switch box were hit by the strike. A woman at the party described what happened: “All of a sudden there was a big bang and people were thrown away from the beer cart. Then there was chaos.” . Around 500 people were at the party when the lightning struck. Many were treated for shock. 
